13/04/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- The trial for the murder of French football fan Brice Taton in Belgrade last year will start on April 21st, local media reported on Monday (April 12th). Fifteen people have been charged in the case. Two of them will be prosecuted in absentia. Taton, 28, a fan of the French football club Toulouse, died in hospital in September 2009 after he was attacked by fans of rival team Partizan Belgrade, ahead of a match between the two squads. (Beta, Politika, RTS, Tanjug, B92 - 12/04/10) 
